Tools / Items Needed:
•	A Laptop computer / workstation with Windows 10 installed.

Step 1: Press windows and r key simultaneously to bring up the Run command dialog box.  
Step 2: Type in “gpedit.msc” without the quotation marks. Press “Ok”.
Step 3: Select Computer Configuraton > Administrative Templates > Windows Components > BitLocker Drive Encryption > Removable Data Drives
Step 4: Right click on “Deny write access to removable drives not protected by BitLocker”.
Step 5: Change value to “Disable”.
Step 6: Exit out of Group Policy Management.
